quarter-bred
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[of wool or progeny] from a sheep comprising three quarters Merino blood and one quarter long wool.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
